President Trump held a meeting in which he heard directly from families who have lost loved ones due to crimes committed by illegal immigrants. The families shared their heartbreaking stories and emphasized the need for stronger border security and immigration policies. The President pledged to take action and ensure that these families' voices are heard. He also highlighted the work of the Victims of Immigrant Crime Engagement (VOICE) office, which provides support and assistance to victims and their families. The President reiterated his commitment to securing the border and ending the immigration crisis.